President Muhammadu Buhari yesterday said the late Baraden Wamakko,  Alhaji Salihu Barade, contributed ‘‘immensely to sustainable peace and unity of Nigeria. He stated this during a condolence visit to the family of the deceased and people of Sokoto State on the demise of the late Senior Counsellor of the Sultanate Council of Sokoto and District Head of Wamakko. The president prayed the Almighty Allah to grant the deceased Aljannat firdaus, and give the family the fortitude to bear the loss. He was represented on the condolence visit by a five-man delegation led by the Minister of Justice, Alhaji Abubakar Malami. Others are; the Minister of Interior, retired Lieutenant -General Abdulrahman Dambazau, that of the Federal Capital Territory (FCT), Alhaji Musa Bello, Chief of Protocol to the President, Ambassador Lawal Abdullahi Kazaure and the Senior Special Assistant to the President, Household, Alhaji Sarki Abba. The All Progressives Congress (APC), gubernatorial candidate, Alhaji Ahmed Aliyu Sokoto, who responded on behalf of the elder brother to the late Barade, Senator Aliyu Wamakko, expressed gratitude for the visit, noting that, “the gesture of the President is an indication of his endless concern for the generality of Nigerians, irrespective of political , cultural,  ethnic or religious affinities .” He added:” This priceless gesture of the Number One citizen of Nigeria would spur us to do more, to ensure the success of all his meaningful, people-oriented policies and programmes.” He described the late Baraden Wamakko as a great man. “We are also consoled by the myriad of nerve and mind soothing condolences from across the globe.”  Buhari arrives Sokoto, promises suitable memorial for Shagari Buhari in Sokoto, promises to immortalise Shagari Buhari condoles Sokoto over Wamakko''s death